                "href": "/profile/Edward-Teach-10"
            },
            "answer_text": "You cannot. There are programs for smartphones called spoofers but if law enforcement turns up the heat enough, they will crack these. A fugitive could conceivably place his/her phone inside a faraday cage, essentially completely cutting off the phone electronically (including the GPS) and would prevent anyone including law enforcement and your cell phone service provider from tracking the phone or even knowing whether or not the phone was still intact or destroyed. As long as the cell phone remained inside it's cage, it couldn't be tracked by anyone no matter where you took it. However, the moment you removed the phone from it's faraday cage to use it, it's exact location would be instantly pinpointed; which renders the whole effort pointless. As Rick and Jon mentioned, this is where 'one-time-use' or burner phones come into play. ",
