            },
            "answer_text": "You can\u2019t. Thanks to technological developments in the wake of 9/11, it can be presumed that if the authorities are tracking your cell phone (if they know that you have one in your name or that you commonly use and they know the cell phone number) if you are a fugitive. Obtaining several pre-paid cell phones, along with new SIM cards, are the best route to go. While these can also be traced, unless you call someone who the police know or suspect that you might contact, they will have to use other methods to track you. It\u2019s probably best to buy these in cash and to do so well in advance of your needing them. Again, your personal cell phone will be compromised if you are being tracked. It\u2019s best that you rid yourself of the device as soon as possible if you are seeking to maintain a low profile. ",
