            "answer_text": "Give it away to someone at the bus station and never use it again. Buy burner phones to use, but don't buy multiple at once, as they could track the purchase after the first one is used, and start tracking the others without you knowing they were compromised. Just buy a phone, use it once, and hand it off to someone else to have.  Better to hand it off, than ditch it.  Pulling the battery and throwing it in the rubbish will stop a tracking, but they'll already know where, and a clean line of dots is less confusing to follow than 10 lines all going in different directions without clarity as to when you had it, and when someone else had it. ",
