                "name": "Burt Andrews",
                "href": "/profile/Burt-Andrews"
            },
            "answer_text": "There is nothing mysterious about cell phones. They are radio transmitters and receivers. If they do not transmit, they can\u2019t be traced. Turn it off, and even detach the battery, if you don\u2019t want to be traced. Simple. But, the moment you power up again, it becomes visible on the net. For long term invisibility, you will need to buy several prepaid cell phones (referred to as \u201cburner\u201d phones). Use each one once and then discard. Even then, if the number you CALL is being monitored, then even your prepaid cell can be back traced. But, by then, you will have left the area you were standing in when you called. Your best method of communications will probably be by using the internet and familiarizing yourself with anonymous servers. These days it is getting harder and harder to communicate without trace. ",
